<%= render :layout => 'projects/project',
  :locals => {:project_title => "quick_scrapper", :project_category => "Rubygem", :project_logo => "quick_scrapper.jpg"} do %>
  quick_scrapper scraps the selection associated to css_selector from a given page.
  quick_scrapper uses the scrapi library to do the scraping, avoiding all the complicated method calls.
  Just one method to do all the scraping required!!<br />
  The download counts of products on this page are actually scrapped from their respective Rubygem pages, using this Rubygem!!
  <div class="synopsis">
    <%= download_count_info("quick_scrapper") %>
    <div class="related_links">
      <span class="helptext">Related Links: </span>
      <%= link_to "Source Code", "https://github.com/bvsatyaram/Quick-Scrapper", :target => "_blank" %>
      <%= link_to "Rubygem Page", "https://rubygems.org/gems/quick_scrapper", :target => "_blank" %>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>